HEADWORD: Descendible
<hw>De*scend"i*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Admitting descent; capable of being descended.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That may descend from an ancestor to an heir.</def>
